From now on, when youaddress each other,

37:18.941 --> 37:21.650
I want you to usephrases like, "I feel..."

37:21.691 --> 37:23.816
(groaning)

37:23.816 --> 37:27.526
Instead of "you, you, you, you."- 'K, fine, fine, fine, fine.

37:27.567 --> 37:29.401
- Uh, excuse me? Your change.

37:29.442 --> 37:33.484
- If we were moving any slower,I'd be frozen in time.

37:33.484 --> 37:35.902
- I'm sorry, I thinkyou shorted me 10 cents.

37:35.943 --> 37:39.652
- Come on, lady. Lady.- I just counted it.Did you drop it?

37:39.652 --> 37:41.402
- Nope.

37:41.443 --> 37:45.153
- I feel... like an item fromthe frozen foods section,

37:45.194 --> 37:48.611
which is way over on the otherside of the grocery store,

37:48.653 --> 37:51.695
would buy us more timethan the produce,

37:51.779 --> 37:53.695
which is right here.- And I'm feeling

37:53.779 --> 37:56.279
like you're telling mewhat to do.

37:56.320 --> 37:59.738
- Just let mehelp him first, then.- Oh, no, I can't wait for that.

37:59.738 --> 38:02.071
I need my dime right now.

38:02.113 --> 38:04.530
- Lady, it's a dime! Let it go.

38:04.571 --> 38:07.656
- OK, fine!(Cinco clears throat.)

38:07.656 --> 38:09.947
I'm sorry, I am owed

38:09.989 --> 38:12.489
and, um, I cannot letthis store cheat me

38:12.489 --> 38:15.531
out of what is rightfully mine.

38:15.572 --> 38:17.198
- OK!

38:17.240 --> 38:19.615
I'm sorry for being so bossy.

38:19.657 --> 38:22.198
- Apology accepted!

38:22.240 --> 38:23.907
Frozen peas it is.

38:23.948 --> 38:25.908
- Nicely done!- Thank you.

38:25.949 --> 38:28.283
- (high-pitched): Nicely done!

38:28.324 --> 38:31.324
Nicely done.

38:31.366 --> 38:33.367
- Carol, you can do it.

38:33.409 --> 38:38.200
- (shaky): May I havea price check of that?

38:39.492 --> 38:42.368
If you don't have time to checkthe price, it's fine.

38:42.410 --> 38:47.368
I mean, if I were doing yourjob, I would be checkingevery price.

38:47.410 --> 38:49.994
- And maybe a pricecomparison, too.

38:50.036 --> 38:53.827
- Yes. We wanna make surewe get the best deal.

38:53.869 --> 38:56.702
- On those peppers.- Mm. Mm-hmm.

38:56.786 --> 38:58.495
- Lady, come on.Let her check me out,

38:58.537 --> 39:01.328
and then you can have yourprecious 10 cents. Please!

39:01.328 --> 39:04.495
I'm going grey!- Maybe you cantake this 10 cents

39:04.578 --> 39:06.746
and things are just gonnawork out just fine.

39:06.788 --> 39:08.538
- Yeah, you know what, lady?That's very nice of you,

39:08.579 --> 39:12.496
but this woman does notdeserve to be bailed out.

39:14.705 --> 39:17.830
- It's just...if you must know, um...

39:17.872 --> 39:20.164
right beforemy favourite uncle died,

39:20.247 --> 39:22.498
he gave me this reallyold dime and, you know,

39:22.540 --> 39:25.415
dimes just have a very specialmeaning to me since that day.

39:25.498 --> 39:28.623
And, you know, I knowit's silly. It's been,like, 10 years and I should be

39:28.665 --> 39:30.999
over it, but... 10!10, like a dime!

39:31.041 --> 39:34.291
See, that...it's really, it's...

39:34.332 --> 39:36.749
Wow!

39:36.791 --> 39:40.583
Oh, OK. Thank you!

39:40.625 --> 39:43.667
- I feel so bad about yourfavourite dead uncle.

39:43.667 --> 39:45.917
(laughing)That was just genius.

39:45.958 --> 39:49.501
- It was absolutely ridiculous.It was the only thingI could come up with

39:49.543 --> 39:52.168
that wouldn't get me locked upfor being certifiably insane.

39:52.168 --> 39:54.126
You were an awfulperson in there.

39:54.168 --> 39:55.960
- Yes, I was.We made a great team.

39:56.002 --> 39:59.252
- OK, everybody.Very, very good work today.

39:59.294 --> 40:02.085
You all took a major stepforward in confronting conflict

40:02.169 --> 40:05.628
in a very public way. You shouldall be very proud of yourself.

40:05.628 --> 40:08.336
- Thanks. Now hand over theprize, so I can take my wife

40:08.378 --> 40:10.420
to the fanciestrestaurant in town.

40:10.461 --> 40:13.837
- Well, according to my timing,Cinco and Lea actually won.

40:13.879 --> 40:16.171
- They won?How is that possible?

40:16.212 --> 40:18.587
- It's possible by four seconds.(guffawing)

40:18.629 --> 40:22.713
- Uh, well, you know, I reallydon't ever have time to eat,

40:22.755 --> 40:24.547
like, ever. So whydon't you take it?

40:24.588 --> 40:27.631
- Oh, oh, guys, before you go,I have a field assignmentfor you.

40:27.673 --> 40:30.881
So, staying in the same teams,I want you guys to go

40:30.923 --> 40:33.548
and confront the person you havethe most conflict with.

40:33.589 --> 40:36.674
Engage with them and payattention to what itis about them

40:36.674 --> 40:39.590
that triggers it in you.- When do we do it?

40:39.632 --> 40:42.007
- Both team members have tohave it done by next week.

40:42.007 --> 40:44.008
So come on, let's go

40:44.050 --> 40:46.008
- Oh, man.

40:46.050 --> 40:49.050
Well, I'm not sure

40:49.133 --> 40:52.967
why you're not excited. I mean,it can't be me, so it must bebecause you heard

40:53.009 --> 40:55.384
the place stinks.- No, actually,

40:55.426 --> 40:58.634
I heard the place is amazing.- Oh.

40:58.676 --> 41:00.802
So then?

41:02.677 --> 41:06.218
- Uh, I guess we could do...I guess we could do lunch.

41:06.260 --> 41:08.343
- We can do lunch, tomorrow.

41:08.385 --> 41:11.553
That's the kindof homework I like.

41:30.221 --> 41:32.305
(knocking)

41:32.346 --> 41:35.681
- Hard at work already, I see.- Hi...

41:35.764 --> 41:38.389
This is a surprise.

41:38.431 --> 41:43.390
Shouldn't you be at work?- Yes, but...

41:43.473 --> 41:45.848
this can't wait.

41:45.848 --> 41:49.265
Lea, I'm sorry things have beenso strained between us lately.

41:49.307 --> 41:53.474
I know I've been busy and you'vebeen stressed out aboutyour book.

41:53.516 --> 41:55.808
- Yeah, a little bit.- Yeah.

41:55.849 --> 41:58.517
Takes me a while to catch onsometimes, but I get it.

41:58.517 --> 42:01.934
And I think I knowwhat you need right now.

42:01.975 --> 42:04.434
- Really?

42:09.851 --> 42:12.310
A laptop?- Yes!

42:12.351 --> 42:14.268
I know your old desktophas been acting up,

42:14.351 --> 42:16.936
and you would never actuallygo and buy one yourself,

42:16.977 --> 42:19.436
so this morningon my way to work,

42:19.477 --> 42:21.561
I decided, what the heck?

42:21.644 --> 42:23.687
And, well, here you are.

42:23.687 --> 42:27.520
- That's really sweet!Thank you.

42:29.437 --> 42:31.271
- Now I really mustget to campus,

42:31.354 --> 42:34.771
but one more thing: I'm takingyou to lunch on Saturday.

42:34.813 --> 42:38.896
- You, me and the laptop?- I'll email you the details.

42:38.938 --> 42:40.855
So what are you up to today?

42:40.897 --> 42:44.397
- You know, justlocked away in here.

42:44.439 --> 42:47.314
Writing.- Then I won't keep you.

42:47.355 --> 42:49.731
I'll see you Saturday.

42:56.441 --> 42:58.607
(piano music plays)

43:00.524 --> 43:04.275
(phone ringing)- Hello?

43:04.317 --> 43:06.650
- How's it going?-

43:06.692 --> 43:09.108
Maybe he's not coming.Is it wrong to hope he forgot?

43:09.150 --> 43:12.150
- Why are you so nervous?- Because my boyfriendjust bought me

43:12.193 --> 43:14.443
a new laptop this morning, andnow I'm sitting in a restaurant,

43:14.484 --> 43:16.943
waiting for another man.- Relax.

43:16.984 --> 43:20.068
It's just a lunch.It's not like it's a date.

43:23.485 --> 43:26.069
Right?- He's here, I gotta go.

43:28.569 --> 43:32.695
- Sorry I'm late.- Hi.

43:32.778 --> 43:36.403
You look--(small laugh)

43:36.445 --> 43:38.737
- Reservations?

43:38.779 --> 43:41.154
- Um...- Um...

43:41.196 --> 43:43.862
We have these guys.- Oh, you know what?

43:43.904 --> 43:46.030
I thought I had mine,but I don't. Darn it. So...

43:46.030 --> 43:47.988
have a great lunch.- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

43:48.030 --> 43:50.613
I'm sure that's not gonnamatter. Will that matter?

43:50.697 --> 43:53.113
- Of course not.

43:54.406 --> 43:57.406
- (whispering): It's not a date.- I'm sorry, what's that?

43:57.448 --> 43:59.781
- Uh, I hear the food's great.

44:01.782 --> 44:04.740
- You know, you baffle mea little bit.

44:04.782 --> 44:07.365
I don't know whya woman like you

44:07.449 --> 44:09.740
is in any way unsure of herself.

44:09.782 --> 44:11.866
- A woman like me?What does that mean?

44:11.866 --> 44:14.366
- You're very smart,you're very, very, funny,

44:14.366 --> 44:17.866
and you don't know you're funny,which makes you even funnier.

44:17.908 --> 44:20.576
- I don't think anybody's evercalled me funny before.

44:20.617 --> 44:22.659
- I think you're a riot.

44:22.701 --> 44:26.535
And, uh... you're really,really pretty.

44:26.577 --> 44:29.077
And you have an effect on me.

44:31.660 --> 44:34.327
I think when two peoplehave things in common,

44:34.368 --> 44:38.703
it helps one to see things inoneself a little more easily.

44:38.703 --> 44:41.203
You know?- You are the last person

44:41.203 --> 44:43.537
I can imagine havingsomething in common with.

44:43.537 --> 44:45.620
- Oh, really?We're both very smart,

44:45.662 --> 44:47.787
we both like to reacha lot of people...

44:47.829 --> 44:49.870
You're prettier than I am.(chuckling)

44:49.912 --> 44:52.205
But, you know,we both have father issues.

44:52.205 --> 44:55.496
- I don't.- Really? Marilynled us right there

44:55.538 --> 44:58.746
and you don't want to admitthat? Well, I admit it.

44:58.830 --> 45:01.581
I have father issues.

45:01.581 --> 45:03.789
- Was your father tough?

45:03.872 --> 45:06.372
- Tough, yes.

45:06.414 --> 45:08.540
Brilliant.

45:08.540 --> 45:10.165
Passionate.

45:10.207 --> 45:12.457
- So what's the problembetween you two?

45:12.540 --> 45:14.748
- We only argue,

45:14.832 --> 45:16.416
so now we don't talk.

